Fallback Method: Use Demo Data: ['Cloud Services', 'On-Premise', 'Consulting', 'Support', 'Training'] with values [85, 60, 45, 30, 15].

Step 1: The Canvas

Initialize fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6)).

Create ax_main covering [0,0,1,1] and turn it off.

Draw white card background.

Step 2: The Chart Layer (Aggressive Shift)

Fix 1: Shift the chart axis WAY to the right. Use ax_chart = fig.add_axes([0.45, 0.2, 0.5, 0.6]). (Start at 45% width).

Turn off axis: ax_chart.axis('off').

Step 3: Plotting

Stems: ax_chart.hlines(y=range(len(items)), xmin=0, xmax=values, color='#E0E0E0', linewidth=3)

Heads (Fix 2): ax_chart.scatter(values, range(len(items)), color='#0078D4', s=800, zorder=3) (Size increased to 800).

Step 4: Labels (The Safe Zone)

Category Names (Left):

Truncate text at 40 characters.

